    DB entity of a group result. A group result defines some properties and who's member in a group of a group study. Members of a GroupResult (or just group) are the StudyResults and not the workers. But a studyResult is always associated with a Worker. A member (StudyResult) can join a group (GroupResult) or leave a group. An active member is a StudyResult who joined a group and is in the activeMemberList. A past member is in the historyMemberList. 'Group result' and 'group' are used interchangeably.
